SHOUT

Syntax: shout <message>

Shouts a message to everyone in your current room -- the same reach as
say. No language is needed; everyone in the room understands a shout
regardless of what language they speak. There is a five-second
cooldown between shouts.

Shout is not a channel and does not reach outside your room. To
coordinate with people elsewhere, use tell (private, one-to-one) or a
carried radio tuned to a shared frequency.

See also: say, ooc, radio
